pull_request.title: Add option to all pytests to skip particular algorithms
pull_request.body:
<!-- Please give a brief explanation of the purpose of this pull request. -->
We have `SKIP_ALGS` available on `test_constant_time.py` but nowhere else.  This adds it to the general test filter alongside `SKIP_TESTS`.  (The method I've used to add it is somewhat brutish, but seems to do the job.)

pull_request.title: Fixup docker interop test
pull_request.body:
pass test even if liboqs does not support all algs reported by interop server.

In this case triggered by interop server (still) supporting more algorithms than `liboqs`.

The error message may be a good place to add/test the [upcoming liboqs(-python) library version string](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs-python/issues/50#issuecomment-1204042998).
